It's defiantly a drastic comparison between the rich and the poor. The rich family of course lived in their own little world and didn't pay too much mind with the Purge as long as they were safe(well at least the son showed some human emotion). But then by the second and third movie we start to see the true agenda of the Purge and it affects the poor.(I'm still thinking about that dad that sold himself to get slaughtered by a bunch of rich people to save his family).
